The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal bunch hails move
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bengal bunch hails move
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: After the Board of Control for Cricket in Indias (BCCI) decision to sit with Indian Cricket League (ICL) authorities in quick time, The Telegraph on Tuesday evening spoke to few former Bengal players who joined the rebel Indian Cricket League (ICL). Elated with the news, all termed it as a positive move by the board and expressed their eagerness for the outcome of the result.         
	The following are what they said (alphabetically):         
	Deep Dasgupta: Its fantastic news. I should congratulate the BCCI for taking up such a decision and sit with the ICL authorities. I am very, very happy This is obviously a nice thing After all the ICL and the players playing here might finally get the recognition.         
	Avishek Jhunjhunwala: I feel on top of the world. There is no bigger news than this in my life now. I hope for the best Hope the ban is lifted and we can be back into mainstream cricket. And if that happens, I hope to start playing for Bengal again. Playing for ICL has obviously improved my cricket and I am a much more matured cricketer now.         
	Shib Sagar Singh: Its great news. I am eagerly waiting for the outcome of the meeting. I am hoping for the best.                                                                                                                          
